column5: Ryan and I put the snowshoes on and ventured out this morning.  We went about 800 yards out and it was a tough go.  Ice thickness ranged from 7" to 3" of hard black ice.  Today wasn't for the faint of heart, but it was well worth it.  Here is a pic of one of Ryan's fish.  Jeff
That's a great fish to have pulled through the ice.  What else did you guys catch?
A few more Walleye and some Jumbo perch.  This one was today's largest.  Jeff
That's a GREAT way to start the ice season!!
Nice walleye can't wait to get down there
Thanks everyone.  This is just the beginning.  Much more eye candy coming soon...
thats crazy, im waiting to pull something of that size through the ice
Great report and pic Jeff  That is one huge walter for sure and real dark colors.... congratulations to Ryan Thanks for sharing Leechman
Ryan knows how to catch nice big fish lol. Congrads!!
Beauty fish Jeff,looks pretty clean and healthy,congrats!!  keep'em coming...
lol love the eye candy!!!!  they sure grow them big in quinte!  cheers!
Great looking eye for sure....was hoping to get down there during the holidays but the forecasted warm temps next week may put a halt to that plan!!...
Nice winter "eye" guys !!!!.  ..well done,and thanks for the ice update as well,i hope to be there soon,looking forward to some more of quintes finest !!!...cheers
nice eye!!! missin them buggers....may can't come quick enough lol....   Hawk
